cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.CY 

This paper discusses privacy protection in the context of web search queries, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques to cluster queries by semantic relatedness (cs.IR), and database management to store and analyze the queries (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper touches upon human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY) in its discussion of user behavior and the impact of TrackMeNot on search engine algorithms.
